This preface is just a placeholder.  When you turn this template into a real book, replace these lines with something warmer. Tell the reader who you’re writing for — whether they’re a student grinding through the material, a colleague borrowing ideas, or just a curious reader poking around. Let them know how you hope they’ll move through the chapters, and whether you’d welcome emails, classroom tests, bug reports, or formal citations.  A little genuine orientation makes even dense technical stuff feel more human.
